    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Unfortunately I don't think `~/.local/bin/` in on PATH by default on most systems. It's easy for us to forget because we've likely added it a long time ago and forgotten. But the only way for a user install to reliably put something on PATH is to modify your `.bashrc` (or `.bash_profile` or `.profile` or one of that mess of files) to change PATH itself. And we can't sanely do that when installing a Python package.\n"
  },
